    notes: "A beginner linear progression program using a 3-tier structure. T1 is your heavy main lift (5x3+, last set AMRAP). T2 is a secondary compound (3x10). T3 is light accessory work (3x15+, last set AMRAP). Add 5 lbs to upper body and 10 lbs to lower body lifts each session. When you fail at T1 5x3, move to 6x2. Fail at 6x2, move to 10x1. Fail at 10x1, test new 5RM and restart. Similar stage progression for T2. Four workouts rotate across 3 days per week (A1, B1, A2, B2).",
